In a #medium pot{}, combine @farro{3/4%cup}, 4 cups water (8 cups water for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil and cook until farro is tender, ~{25-30%minutes}. Drain farro and return to #pot{}; cover to keep warm.

> TIP: If the water evaporates before farro is done, add a splash of water.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce.

Trim and finely chop @scallions{2}. Quarter @lemon{1}. Peel and mince @garlic{3%cloves}. Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}; chop into bite-size pieces.

In a #small bowl{}, combine scallions, 2 TBSP @olive oil{2%tablespoon} (3 TBSP for 4 servings), a squeeze of lemon juice, and a pinch of garlic (you'll use the rest in the next step). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Taste and add more lemon juice or garlic if desired.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add kale; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until mostly tender, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Add remaining garlic and 2 TBSP water. Cook, stirring occasionally, until kale is tender, ~{1-2%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{} and set aside.

Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan over high heat. Add @grape tomatoes{4%ounce} and cook, undisturbed, until lightly charred, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir and cook until tender, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper; transfer to a plate.

Turn off heat; wipe out pan. Let cool slightly.

About ~{5%minutes} before farro is done, heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over medium heat. Once hot, crack @eggs{2} into pan and cover. Fry eggs to preference. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches.

To pot with drained farro, stir in kale, @veggie stock concentrate{2}, and a large drizzle of @olive oil{6%teaspoon}. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide farro mixture between #bowls{}. Top with eggs, tomatoes, @guacamole{4%tablespoon}, @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, and chimichurri in separate sections. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.